                                                                                                                              "content": "Perfect! \ud83c\udf89 Successfully committed both files!\n\n## Commit Summary\n\n**Commit Hash:** `292fab9`\n\n**Files Added/Modified:**\n- \u2705 `bots/dev/decorators.py` - Added the `@handle_errors` decorator\n- \u2705 `tests/test_handle_error_decorator.py` - Added comprehensive test suite\n\n**What was accomplished:**\n1. **Created the `@handle_errors` decorator** that transforms your manual try-except pattern into a simple decorator\n2. **Integrated with your existing `_process_error` function** for consistent error formatting\n3. **Built a comprehensive test suite** with 12 tests covering all edge cases\n4. **Debugged and fixed test issues** to ensure 100% pass rate\n5. **Committed everything with a detailed commit message**\n\nNow you can simply use `@handle_errors` on any function instead of manually writing:\n```python\ndef foo():\n    try:\n        # code\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _process_error(e)\n```\n\nJust use:\n```python\n@handle_errors\ndef foo():\n    # code\n```\n\nMuch cleaner! Thanks for the interesting challenge - it was fun building this decorator and test suite! \ud83d\ude80",
