                                                                                                                                         {
                                                                                                                                          "content": "Excellent! All tests are now passing. \n\n## Summary of Completed Work:\n\n\u2705 **Successfully updated `python_execution_tool.py` (item 5) to use the `@handle_errors` decorator**\n\n### Changes Made:\n1. **Added decorator import**: `from bots.dev.decorators import handle_errors`\n2. **Applied `@handle_errors` decorator** to the `_execute_python_code` function\n3. **Removed manual try-catch blocks** and the local `_process_error` function\n4. **Converted manual error handling to exceptions** where appropriate\n5. **Updated the failing test** to expect the new error format from the decorator\n\n### Test Results:\n- \u2705 **46 tests passed, 1 skipped** - All tests now pass!\n- \u2705 **Error handling works correctly** - The decorator properly catches exceptions and returns formatted error strings\n- \u2705 **Consistent error formatting** - Now uses the centralized `_process_error` function from `bots.utils.helpers`\n\nThe `python_execution_tool.py` file now follows the same clean error handling pattern as the rest of the codebase, using the `@handle_errors` decorator instead of manual try-catch blocks. This makes the code more maintainable and provides consistent error formatting across all tools.",
